# CODEOWNERS — review routing only, NOT the enforcement mechanism.
#
# Per docs/AGENT_PLAN.md §4.1 and §4.3, the file-ownership matrix is
# enforced by the role-guard CI (`.githooks/role-guard.sh` +
# `.github/workflows/ci.yml`), which reads three forge-neutral signals:
# PR label → branch prefix → commit trailer. CODEOWNERS exists only so
# GitHub routes review notifications to the right human (the
# Orchestrator) when paths in the matrix change.
#
# Agent personas are not separate GitHub identities — they are roles
# encoded in PR labels (`role:<role>`), branch prefixes (`research/`,
# `test/`, `dev/<slice>/`, `review/`, `audit/`, `chore/`), and
# `X-Bier-Role:` commit trailers. The single human/machine account
# (`@milmazz`) drives every persona. The role-guard CI determines
# which role authored the PR and which globs that role may touch.

# spec/ — Researcher (RW); Tester/Developer/Orchestrator read-only.
spec/                              @milmazz  # role: researcher
priv/repo/conformance_fixtures.sql @milmazz  # role: tester (Postgres fixtures)

# test/ — Tester (RW); Developer/Orchestrator read-only.
test/                              @milmazz  # role: tester
test/support/                      @milmazz  # role: tester

# lib/ — Developer (RW); Tester/Orchestrator read-only.
lib/                               @milmazz  # role: developer

# Build configuration — shared between Tester (test-only deps) and
# Developer (runtime deps); Orchestrator arbitrates.
mix.exs                            @milmazz  # role: developer + tester (split: test-only vs runtime deps)
mix.lock                           @milmazz  # role: developer + tester

# Orchestrator-only.
docs/STATUS.md                     @milmazz  # role: orchestrator
docs/AGENT_PLAN.md                 @milmazz  # role: orchestrator
.github/                           @milmazz  # role: orchestrator (CI, CODEOWNERS, templates)
.githooks/                         @milmazz  # role: orchestrator
.claude/agents/                    @milmazz  # role: orchestrator (subagent definitions)
mise.toml                          @milmazz  # role: orchestrator
.formatter.exs                     @milmazz  # role: orchestrator
.credo.exs                         @milmazz  # role: orchestrator
.gitignore                         @milmazz  # role: orchestrator
docker-compose.yml                 @milmazz  # role: orchestrator
CLAUDE.md                          @milmazz  # role: orchestrator
README.md                          @milmazz  # role: orchestrator
LICENSE                            @milmazz  # role: orchestrator

# CHANGELOG.md is RW for every role — one [Unreleased] entry per PR
# (enforced by the changelog gate, not by CODEOWNERS).
CHANGELOG.md                       @milmazz
